{"title_page": "Milford Ice Pavilion", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=November 2018}}\n{{Infobox venue |\n  stadium_name     = Milford Ice Pavilion|\n  nickname         = The House that Marty Built|\n  image            = |\n  location         = 291 Bic Dr<br>Milford, CT 06460|\n  broke_ground     = |\n  opened           = 1975|\n  closed           = |\n  demolished       = |\n  owner            = Milford Ice Pavilion|\n  operator         = |\n  surface          = |\n  construction_cost= |\n  architect        = |\n  former_names     = |\n  tenants          = [[Sacred Heart Pioneers men's ice hockey|Sacred Heart Pioneers]] (1993-2016)<br>[http://www.turtleshockey.com Turtles Hockey]<br>[http://www.milfordindianshockey.com Milford Indians (High School Hockey)]|\n  seating_capacity  = 1,000 (hockey) \n}}\n\n'''Milford Ice Pavilion''' is a 1,000-seat skating rink in [[Milford, Connecticut]]. It is home to the Milford Indians co-op high school team, and [[Sacred Heart University]] [[Sacred Heart Pioneers men's ice hockey|Pioneers men's ice hockey team]] until 2016.  The building opened in 1975 and was renovated in 1985.  It also serves several local hockey high school and club level teams.  It has been the home of the Sacred Heart hockey program since its inception in 1993.\n\nIts sister facility was the [[Northford Ice Pavilion]] in [[North Branford, Connecticut]].  However, ownership of the Milford Ice recently changed and the two facilities no longer are related (except for the snack bars).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hartfordbusiness.com/article/20180829/NEWHAVENBIZ/180829903/milford-ice-pavilion-changes-hands|title=Milford Ice Pavilion changes hands|publisher=hartford business.com|accessdate=December 16, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.milfordice.com/}}\n\n{{Atlantic Hockey}}\n{{Sacred Heart Pioneers men's ice hockey navbox}}\n{{Sacred Heart University}}\n{{coord|41.216378|-73.091424|display=t|type:landmark}}\n\n[[Category:Sports venues completed in 1975]]\n[[Category:Sacred Heart Pioneers ice hockey]]\n[[Category:College ice hockey venues in the United States]]\n[[Category:Indoor ice hockey venues in the United States]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Milford, Connecticut]]\n[[Category:Sports venues in New Haven County, Connecticut]]\n[[Category:1975 establishments in Connecticut]]\n\n\n{{Connecticut-stadium-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Refimprove|date=November 2018}}\n{{Infobox_Stadium |\n  stadium_name     = Milford Ice Pavilion|\n  nickname         = The House that Marty Built|\n  image            = |\n  location         = 291 Bic Dr<br>Milford, CT 06460|\n  broke_ground     = |\n  opened           = 1975|\n  closed           = |\n  demolished       = |\n  owner            = Milford Ice Pavilion|\n  operator         = |\n  surface          = |\n  construction_cost= |\n  architect        = |\n  former_names     = |\n  tenants          = [[Sacred Heart Pioneers men's ice hockey|Sacred Heart Pioneers]] (1993-2016)<br>[http://www.turtleshockey.com Turtles Hockey]<br>[http://www.milfordindianshockey.com Milford Indians (High School Hockey)]|\n  seating_capacity  = 1,000 (hockey) \n}}\n\n'''Milford Ice Pavilion''' is a 1,000-seat skating rink in [[Milford, Connecticut]]. It is home to the Milford Indians co-op high school team, and [[Sacred Heart University]] [[Sacred Heart Pioneers men's ice hockey|Pioneers men's ice hockey team]] until 2016.  The building opened in 1975 and was renovated in 1985.  It also serves several local hockey high school and club level teams.  It has been the home of the Sacred Heart hockey program since its inception in 1993. \n\nIts sister facility was the [[Northford Ice Pavilion]] in [[North Branford, Connecticut]].  However, ownership of the Milford Ice recently changed and the two facilities no longer are related (except for the snack bars).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hartfordbusiness.com/article/20180829/NEWHAVENBIZ/180829903/milford-ice-pavilion-changes-hands|title=Milford Ice Pavilion changes hands|publisher=hartford business.com|accessdate=December 16, 2018}}</ref>\n\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}} \n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.milfordice.com/}}\n\n{{Atlantic Hockey}}\n{{Sacred Heart Pioneers men's ice hockey navbox}}\n{{Sacred Heart University}}\n{{coord|41.216378|-73.091424|display=t|type:landmark}}\n\n[[Category:Sports venues completed in 1975]]\n[[Category:Sacred Heart Pioneers ice hockey]]\n[[Category:College ice hockey venues in the United States]]\n[[Category:Indoor ice hockey venues in the United States]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Milford, Connecticut]]\n[[Category:Sports venues in New Haven County, Connecticut]]\n[[Category:1975 establishments in Connecticut]]\n\n\n{{Connecticut-stadium-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Joeykai", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Milford_Ice_Pavilion"}
